	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002169_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 47 top left--><!--Hand 02 68010 superscript E top right--><!--headed notepaper--><!-- <p rend="center"><hi rend="italic">Newstead Abbey,</hi></p>
<p rend="center"><hi rend="italic">Mansfield, Notts.</hi></p>--><!--end of headed notepaper-->
				<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>25 <choice><abbr>Jany</abbr><expan>January</expan></choice> 1865</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Captain Chapman</p>
				<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I write a line just 
<lb/>to say Welcome home 
<lb/>again to Old England 
<lb/>and to add I con-
<lb break="no"/>-gratulate you on 
<lb/>your success 
<lb/>with the "America" 
<lb/>I trust you found 
<lb/>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> C. and all 
<lb/>your friends as 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002169_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>well as you could wish.</p>
<lb/><p>I am in the labour 
<lb/>pains of composing 
<lb/>another book and 
<lb/>will take the 
<lb/>liberty of sending 
<lb/>you a copy as 
<lb/>soon as it is out 
<lb/>as a sort of 
<lb/><unclear cert="high">thank </unclear> offering for 
<lb/>your kindness to 
<lb/>me and to my 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002169_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>"Portuguese servant" 
<lb/>by whom by the way 
<lb/>I was informed 
<lb/>this morning of 
<lb/>your address.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">With my best 
<lb/>now to your 
<lb/>good lady and 
<lb/>all manner of 
<lb/>good wishes for 
<lb/>your health and 
<lb/>happiness</p>
<lb/><p>I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">David Livingstone</p>
			
</div>
